  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.header": "Setting up and using the Keyboard Relay",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_1": "The Keyboard Relay is used to play your organ in real time using a MIDI keyboard",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_2": "You can set it up by pressing the '%s' key...",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_3": "...then selecting your MIDI keyboard and clicking the save icon",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_4": "You can specify a redstone frequency for a particular MIDI channel by Sneaking and Right-Clicking, then putting an item in the correct slot",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_5": "Activate it by Right-Clicking",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_6": "Now, all the notes you play on your MIDI keyboard...",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.keyboard_relay_setup.text_7": "...will trigger the corresponding redstone links!",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.header": "Note Link Basics",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_1": "Note Links are a kind of Redstone Link that let you transmit and receive musical notes",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_10": "Use the top slot to designate different groups of links",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_11": "Place an item in the slot to specify the group",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_12": "F4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_13": "D4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_14": "A#3",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_15": "Note Links will transmit Redstone signals to other Note Links with the same pitch and the same group",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_16": "They can also interface with the Tracker Bar...",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_17": "...and the Keyboard Relay",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_18": "Simply set the MIDI channel in the block's GUI, and it will automatically activate the correct Note Links",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_19": "Note Links are backwards-compatible with Redstone Links via the Legacy Frequency Map. You can find a chart for it online",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_2": "Like Redstone Links, Note Links can transmit redstone signals wirelessly within 256 blocks",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_3": "Right-click while Sneaking to toggle receive mode",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_4": "A simple Right-click with a Wrench can do the same",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_5": "The bottom slot on the Note Link lets you select a note to receive or transmit",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_6": "Hold right-click and select the desired note from the menu",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_7": "F4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_8": "D4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_basics.text_9": "A#3",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.header": "Setting up Note Links with the Clipboard",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_1": "Like Redstone Links, you can use a Clipboard to copy settings between Note Links",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_10": "D#4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_2": "C4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_3": "C4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_4": "If you edit a Note Link's settings with a Clipboard in your offhand, it will automatically copy the settings",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_5": "D4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_6": "The next Note Link you place while holding this Clipboard will be one semitone higher",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_7": "D#4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_8": "E4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.note_link_cap.text_9": "Or, you can Sneak to make the next Note Link a semitone lower",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.header": "Adjusting a pipe's pitch",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_1": "Pipes can be placed on Windchests and Fluid Tanks",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_2": "If the Windchest is configured correctly...",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_3": "...or, alternatively, if the tank receives sufficient heat...",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_4": "...the Pipe will play a note when activated",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_5": "Use the corresponding Pipe item on the block to lower its pitch",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_6": "Cycle between five different octaves using a Wrench",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_7": "Engineer's Goggles can help to find out the current pitch and octave of a Pipe",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_adjusting.text_8": "C#4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_swapping.header": "Swapping different pipes",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_swapping.text_1": "You can instantly change the type of a Pipe by using another Pipe's item on it",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_swapping.text_2": "However, if the new pipe is too long, blocks can get in the way",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_swapping.text_3": "To fix this, simply remove any blocks that are in the way.",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.pipe_swapping.text_4": "The same goes for horizontal pipes",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.header": "Playing music rolls",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_1": "The Tracker Bar is used to play MIDI files from music rolls",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_2": "Each channel in the MIDI file is represented by a redstone frequency",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_3": "This frequency is used when the Tracker Bar plays a note on that MIDI channel",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_4": "When playing a note, it will activate any note links that match the note and assigned frequency",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_5": "F4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_6": "F4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_7": "Each channel can use a unique frequency to play different pipes",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_8": "D4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.tracker_bar.text_9": "D4",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.header": "Using Windchests",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_1": "Windchests allow you to toggle several pipes at once",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_2": "The Windchests must be placed with the red arrow pointing toward the Windchest Controller",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_3": "Then place a fan blowing air into the Windchest Controller",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_4": "When the Controller is powered by redstone...",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_5": "... its attached Windchests will activate",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_6": "Now, any pipes attached to the Windchests will sound when powered by redstone",
  "pipeorgans.ponder.windchests.text_7": "... as long as the Windchest Controller has power",
